meanings.english_definition: A former group of liverworts, now considered obsolete.

etymology.value: From Ancient Greek ἀν- (an-, “not”) + ἄκρος (ákros, “summit, top”) + γυνή (gunḗ, “woman”) + -αι (-ai, plural suffix).

usage_notes.explanation: This term is no longer in common use in modern botany.
